  <subsection xml:id="subsec-units-of-measuring-time">
    <title>Units of measuring time</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>
       <url href="https://youtu.be/RBvmO7NgUp0" />
      </p>
      <p>
        Units of mesurering time are;
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Minutes
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Hours
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Seconds
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </introduction>
    
    
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Convertin-hours-to-minutes">
      <title>Converting hours to minutes</title>
      <p>
        <m>1</m> hour <m>=</m> <m>60</m> minutes.
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in pairs.
        </p>
        <sidebyside>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Whate you need.
                </p>
                <p>
                  razer blade,manniler paper(white and yellow), 
                  black maker pen,a wire and a pair of campus.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>Make a clock face like the one shown 
              alongside using a paper cut out.</li>
              <li>Move the minute hand clockwise to make 
              a complete turn.</li>
              <li>How many minutes does the minuite 
              hand cover in one complete turn?</li>
              <li>Observe how the hour hand moves 
              when the minute hand make one complete turn. 
              What have you noticed?</li>
              <li>Share your findings with other learners in class.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <image source="/Exampl-1.png" width="40%">
            <shortdescription>Clock</shortdescription>
          </image>
        </sidebyside>
        <p>
          Learning point.
        </p>
        <p>
          From the above activity you should notice that;
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>1</m> hour <m>=</m> <m>60</m> minutes.
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Convert <m>3</m> hours
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
          <p>
            Conversion of hours to minutes, we use the 
            conversion units that is <m>1 \, hour \,= \,60 \,minuites </m>.
          </p>
        </hint>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1 \, hour =\amp 60 \, minutes</mrow>
              <mrow> 3 \, hours =\amp (3 \times 60)\, minutes </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 180 \, minutes </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>3\, hours = 180 \, minutes</m>
          </p>
          
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            How many minuites are the in <m>3\frac{1}{2}</m> hours?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <m>1 \, hour = 60 \, minutes</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 3\frac{1}{2}\,hours=\amp (3\frac{1}{2} \times 60) \, minutes</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp (\frac{7}{2} \times 60) \, minutes</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp \frac{420}{2} \,minuites</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 210 \, minutes</mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>3\frac{1}{2}\,hours= 210 \, minutes </m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A motorist took <m>8 \, hours </m> to travel from Kilifi 
            to Machakos. How many minutes did he take during the travel?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Hours he took was <m>8 \, hours</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            To convert the hours taken to minuites, use 
            <m>1 \, hour=60 \, minutes</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 8 \, hours=\amp(8 \times 60)minutes </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 480\, minutes </mrow>
              
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            The minutes taken for the travel is <m> 480\, minutes</m>
          </p>
  
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-minutes-into-hours">
      <title>Converting minutes into hours</title>
      <p>
        As discused before that <m>1\,hour=60 \, minutes</m>.
        it's clear to see also that <m>60 \, minutes=1\,hour</m>.
      
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in groups.
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Grade 7 learners recorded the time 
                they spent doing various activities during their 
                leisure time.
              </p>
              <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                <row header="no" >
                  <cell>Name</cell>
                  <cell>Activity</cell>
                  <cell>Time taken in minutes</cell>
                  <cell>Time taken in hours</cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell>Moraa</cell>
                  <cell>Running</cell>
                  <cell>120</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell>Akinyi</cell>
                  <cell>Playing football</cell>
                  <cell>90</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell>Ekadeli</cell>
                  <cell>Reading story books</cell>
                  <cell>60</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
            </li>
            <li>Why should we engage in positive leisure activity?</li>
            <li>Fill in the table to show the time spent by each learner in hours.</li>
            <li>Share your work with other learners in class.</li>
            
           
          </ol>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A bus took <m>560 \, minutes </m> to travel from Kisumu 
            to Nairobi. What time did it take in hours and minutes?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            The bus took <m>560\, minutes</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            Note that, <m>60 \, minutes=1\,hour</m>
          </p>
          <sidebyside>
            <p>
              <md>
                <mrow> 560 \, minutes=\amp (560 \div 60)hours</mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp 9 \, hours \, 20 \, minutes </mrow>
                <mrow> \amp </mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
            <tabular>
              <row>
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">9 hours</cell>
                
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell right="medium">60</cell>
                <cell>560</cell>
                <cell></cell>
               
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">-540</cell>
                
              </row>
              <row halign="right">
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">20 mins</cell>
                
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </sidebyside>
          <p>
            The bus took <m>9 \, hours \, 20 \, minutes</m> 
            to travel from Kisumu to Nairobi.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-minutes-into-seconds">
      <title>Converting minutes into seconds</title>
      <p>
        The statment for conversion states that,
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>1 \, minute \,= 60 \, seconds</m>.
      </p>
      <activity>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Using a stopwatch or a rist watch or a clock watch, 
                  observe and record the number of seconds in the following 
                  minutes.
                </p>
                <tabular halign="right" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                  <row header="no">
                    <cell>Minutes</cell>
                    <cell>Seconds</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>1 minute</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>3 minutes</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes"> 
                    <cell>5 minutes</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>10 minutes</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular>
              </li>
              <li>How many seconds are there in a minutes?</li>
              <li>Share your findings with other learners in class.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <sidebyside>
            <p>
              a).Convert <m>12 \, minutes </m> into seconds.
            </p>
            <p>
              b). Owilii took <m>5 \, minutes \,24 \, seconds</m> 
            to walk from the classroom to the school gate. 
            How nuch time did she take in seconds to reach the school gate?
            </p>
          </sidebyside>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            a).
          </p>
        
          <p >
            <md>
              <mrow > 1 \, minute=\amp 60 \ seconds </mrow>
              <mrow>12 \, minutes= \amp 12 \times 60 \, seconds </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp  720 \, seconds</mrow>
              <mrow> \text{Therefor,} \, 12 \, minutes=\amp  720 \, seconds</mrow>
                 
            </md>
              
          </p>
          <p>
            b).
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1 \, minutes= \amp 60 \,seconds </mrow>
              <mrow> 5 \, minutes \, 24 \, seconds=\amp  5 \, 
              minutes+ 24 \, seconds</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp (5 \times 60)\, seconds + 24 \, seconds </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 300 \, seconds + 24 \, seconds </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp 324 \, seconds </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
           
           
          
        </solution>
      </example>
      
      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-second-into-minutes">
      <title>Converting second into minutes.</title>
      <p>
        Converting seconds into minutes depend on the previous sub-topic. 

      </p>
      <p>
        Notice that, <m>60 \, seconds = 1 \,minutes</m>
      </p>
      <activity>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Using a stopwatch or a rist watch or a clock watch, 
                  observe and record the number of minutes in the following 
                  seconds.
                </p>
                <tabular halign="right" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                  <row header="no">
                    <cell>Seconds</cell>
                    <cell>Minutes</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>60 seconds</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>120 seconds</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>180 seconds</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes"> 
                    <cell>240 seconds</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                  <row header="yes">
                    <cell>300 seconds</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular>
              </li>
              <li>Share your work with other learners in class.</li>
              
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A digital game took <m>200 \, seconds</m>. How long did 
            the digital game take in munites and seconds?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <sidebyside>
            <p>
              <md>
                <mrow> 60 \, seconds=\amp 1 \, minutes </mrow>
                <mrow> 200 \, seconds=\amp (200 \div 60) \, minutes </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp 3 \, munites 20 \, seconds</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
            <tabular>
              <row>
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">3 minutes</cell>
                
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell right="medium">60</cell>
                <cell>200</cell>
                <cell></cell>
               
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">-180</cell>
                
              </row>
              <row halign="right">
                <cell></cell>
                <cell bottom="medium">20 seconds</cell>
                
              </row>
            </tabular>
  
          </sidebyside>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            The digital game took <m>3 \, minutes \, 20 \, seconds</m>
          </p>

        </solution>
      </example>

      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-hours-into-seconds">
      <title>Converting hours into seconds</title>
      <p>
        By the conversion above for minutes to hours,seconds to minutes,etc,
      </p>
      <p>
        Convertion of  hours to second, use <m>1 \, hour =3600 \,seconds</m>.
      </p>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Convert <m>7 \, hours </m> to seconds.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            if <m>1 \, hour = 3\,600 \, seconds</m>, Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow>7 \, hours= \amp (7 \times 3\,600)\,seconds </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 25\,200 \, seconds </mrow>
              
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>7 \, hours= 25\,200 \, seconds</m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Morara covered  a certain distance in <m>2 \, hours</m>. How 
            long did the journey take in seconds?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            If <m>1 \, hour = 3\,600 \, seconds</m>, therefore, 
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 2 \, hours = \amp (2 \times 3\,600) \, seconds </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 7\,200  \, seconds</mrow>
              
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            The journey took <m>7\,200 \, seconds</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-second-into-hours">
      <title>Converting second into hours</title>
      <p>
        As stated earlier that, <m>1 \, hour = 3\,600 \, seconds</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        It also implies that, <m>3\,600 \, seconds= 1 \, hour</m>.
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in groups of 4
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Fill in the table below. You may use a calculator to work out 
                the division.
              </p>
              <tabular halign="right" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                <row header="no">
                  <cell>Seconds</cell>
                  <cell>Minutes</cell>
                  <cell>Hours</cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell><m>3\,600</m></cell>
                  <cell><m>60</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell><m>7\,200</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell><m>10\,800</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell><m>14\,400</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Share your answer with other learners in your class.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Convert <m>10\,800 \, seconds</m> into hours.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            If <m>3\,600 \, sedconds = 1\,hour</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow>10\,800 \, seconds= \amp (10\,800 \div 3\, 600) hours </mrow>
              <mrow> = \amp 3\, hours </mrow>

            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>10\,800 \, seconds = 3 \, hours</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
       
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Baya spent <m>7\,200 \, seconds </m> seconds washing clothes. 
            How much time did he spend in hours?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 3\,600 \, seconds=\amp 1 \, hour </mrow>
              <mrow> 7\,200 \, seconds =\amp (7 \, 200 \div 3\, 600)\, hours</mrow>
              <mrow> = \amp 2 \, hours </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            Baya spent <m>2 \, hours</m> washing clothes.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>

    
